This paper deals with the problem of uncoordinated spectrum access, which is a topic in the field of wireless communication and networking. The use of multi-armed bandit algorithms is a common approach in this field, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of multiple users accessing the same spectrum, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of stochastic algorithms and the analysis of their performance suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of bandit algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
